    <h2>What CPS Do You Need for Minecraft PvP?</h2>
    <p>Click speed is one of the most discussed stats in Minecraft PvP. But how much CPS do you actually need? The answer depends heavily on which version of Minecraft you're playing and what game mode you're in.</p>

    <h3>Minecraft Java Edition 1.8 PvP — The Most CPS-Dependent Version</h3>
    <p>The legendary 1.8 combat system removes the attack cooldown present in modern versions, making raw CPS directly tied to DPS (damage per second). In 1.8 PvP, every click that connects deals damage, so more clicks equals more damage — there's no mechanical cap. The recommended CPS for competitive 1.8 PvP is <strong>10–16 CPS</strong>. Below 8 CPS and you'll struggle against practiced opponents. Above 14 CPS, you're in elite territory.</p>

    <h3>Minecraft Java Edition 1.9+ PvP — CPS Matters Less</h3>
    <p>Post-1.9 combat introduced a weapon cooldown system where hitting too quickly reduces your damage. The optimal attack speed is 1 click per cooldown cycle — roughly 1–4 CPS depending on the weapon. Raw CPS is far less important here. Focus on accurate, well-timed single clicks rather than maximum click rate.</p>

    <h3>Hypixel BedWars CPS Requirements</h3>
    <p>BedWars uses modern combat, so extremely high CPS won't help much during actual sword fights. However, CPS matters for bridge building speed, where faster clicking means faster block placement. For competitive BedWars bridging, <strong>8–12 CPS</strong> is sufficient. Most serious BedWars players aim for 8–10 CPS.</p>

    <h3>Server Anti-Cheat CPS Limits</h3>
    <p>Most major servers have anti-cheat systems that flag unusually high CPS. Hypixel's anti-cheat typically flags at 18–20+ CPS. Other servers may flag as low as 15 CPS. Playing at 10–14 CPS keeps you under radar on virtually all servers while still being highly competitive.</p>

    <h3>How to Reach 10+ CPS for Minecraft</h3>
    <p>If you're currently at 6–8 CPS and want to reach 10+, the most reliable paths are: (1) daily practice with our <a href="/">CPS test</a> for 2–4 weeks, (2) learning jitter clicking, (3) upgrading to a gaming mouse. Most players can reach 10 CPS within 4–6 weeks of dedicated practice starting from the 6 CPS baseline.</p>

